The paper deals with wireless relay networks and their capacity, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of bidirected edges and cycles in the network suggests a systems and control theory (cs.SY) perspective. The paper also mentions interference, which is a common issue in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the identification of information carrying links and feedback links could be seen as a machine learning (cs.LG) problem.
